        <TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=133 COLSPAN=3>
                    
                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-06-11 - Gorden Tid Bits</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <span class="newstext">
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/050597.html"><b>Zone
    Names</b></a><br>
    Weve no plans to change the file names for the zones (which is what
    controls whats in the /who all list). Some of the earlier zones did use a
    strange naming convention, but for the most part, most of them are pretty
    close to its RP name. The strange ones are easily memorized after a bit of
    play.<br>
    <br>
    qey2hh1 is West Karana, qeytoqrg is Qeynos Hills, qrg is Surefall Glade.
    qcat is Qeynos Catacombs.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/050644.html"><b>Top
    10 Biggest Improvements in EQ</b></a><br>
    Thanks Hooml2, Ive got a few myself off the top of my head. Not sure
    whered Id fit them in:<br>
    <br>
    Rogue hide/sneak vs. living and dead<br>
    Rogue evade<br>
    Shrink<br>
    Clarity<br>
    Sit-n-Med<br>
    Halfed experience loss on death<br>
    Additional HP regen for characters based on class and level.<br>
    HPs upped for a bunch of classes<br>
    /corpse<br>
    Contextual randomization of Kunark loot.<br>
    Emote anims.<br>
    Jewelrycraft revamp (my vote for &quot;EQs Best Tradeskill&quot;)<br>
    Ok, Im tired now. I have a complete list at the office, but not every
    change, even if for the better, could fit into the top 10.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/050582.html"><b>Test
    of Mystics</b></a><br>
    <i>[Quote from original post: Your pet doesnt go poof like that. You can
    bet as an enchanter Id summon my pet and Aanyas him. Of course, if it is
    held in the arena, pet suicides anyway.]</i><br>
    <br>
    Not any more, we ninjaenhanced it :)<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/050579.html"><b>Another
    Broken Quest?</b></a><br>
    I believe this quest was reported in the &quot;Broken Quests&quot; thread
    started by QwinnofTunare. One of our testers is all over that thread and
    hand-carrying the issues there up to the designer who can fix it.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047146-8.html"><b>Gordon
    on Huge Wizard Thread</b></a><br>
    Before I close the thread due to its size, did want to make a small comment:<br>
    <br>
    Im sorry all, but the wizard issues brought up in this post and others have
    been addressed in the past. Wizards are not broken, and I am indeed sorry if
    you do not agree with our stance.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/050396.html"><b>Rez
    Bug</b></a><br>
    Though there was a problem a few months ago that had GM resurrections (and
    all other resurrections for that matter) returning less experience than they
    should, it was corrected.<br>
    <br>
    I do apologize to those who had to deal with the Rez bug, even when getting
    rezd for a bug.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048335.html"><b>Crescent
    Armor in Kunark</b></a><br>
    Armor in Kunark was typically only made NODROP if it was to be used as a
    component in a quest. Now I dont know off the top of my head if that is
    what was planned for this armor, but Ill look into it on Monday.</li>
</ul>
